Oct 10 2005	Nice hotel-thin floors=nightime voices	We stayed here in late August for a family get together nearby and while not cheap it was considerably cheaper and more convenient than the downtown hotels. The hotel itself is quite well kept and has a greeat deal of charm. I am not from a &quot;big city&quot; and must tell you that I did not feel uncomfortable in the neighborhood at night. There were many people out and about. I was in town the weekend of the Chicago Air and Water show and it was great to walk about a mile to the western end of the lakefront to see the air portion with flybys of all the combat jets! The hotel itself had mostly good points: Its quite clean-at least on the 2nd floor and our suite room with 2 double beds and a sofa bed was plenty of space for 2 adults and 2 children. They would be wise to add a second tv for the other side of the room though. The hotel is situated in the &quot;boys town&quot; area of Chicago so if you are not a fan of alternative lifestyles you may want to pass on this hotel. The ceiling/floors are pretty thin and at 2:00am you can hear any lovers quarel within a few rooms. Not the hotels fault for rude/unruly guests, but I was very offended by what I heard. Hotel management gave the standard theres nothing we could do although it went on for more than 30 minutes. Parking is impossible so prepare to hand your keys over to the garage next door although you can come and go with a ticket from the hotels front desk. Beds were very comfy and extra pillows were already in the room. Breakfast was standard fare and kids don't mind that! Would I go back? Yes because of location although I would ask for a room on the top floor and deal with the terribly slow elevator.	
Sep 12 2005	Very Cute Hotel! Loved It	My husband and I stayed at this hotel on August 29th through August 31, 2005. We were visiting Chicago as a little getaway for my birthday! We had tickets to a Cubs game and this hotel was perfect because it is only like 5 Blocks from Wrigleyfield. The hotel is in a great location if you want to experience Chicago without all of the hustle &amp; bustle of being downtown. There were several little bars and restuarants all within walking distance and Lake Michigan was only about 2 blocks away! We actually spent alot of our time just walking around the neighborhoods and enjoying all of the views of the old homes &amp; historic buildings. The hotel itself was so cute! It was very small and had a more of a bed and breakfast feel about it. I would reccomend this hotel to visitors young and old! It was a great choice!	
Aug 11 2005	If you love Ashtrays and poor customer service	This was the worst hotel I stayed at in Chicago! If you are looking for a hotel to smoke in, this is your dream hotel. If you want a manager who is all about making your stay the worst possible experience Manager Stephen Hampton is your guy. Rather than write an essay about how terrible my experience was here just do your self a favor and stay at another place. If you want something in this neighborhood with great service, clean rooms and quaint charm I recommend the Majestic Hotel just up the street (528 West Brompton). Seriously do yourself and loved ones a favor and avoid this hotel!	
